excellent, even without the fennel, which we didn't have. served with rice, and wished we had made more sauce!

Rating: 4
This is a deceptively simple dish. I think the amount of hot pepper may be a misprint; 3/4 tsp was fine. It gave a nice warmth without searing. I made this in March, when tomatoes are sad, but it didn't seem to matter. Used a large fennel and a very large onion and a lot less feta, maybe a quarter cup. I also halved the oil for the vegetables and served it with penne. It was terrific! My husband decided to have more instead of dessert. This is company worthy.

Rating: 4
This dish is wonderfully simple and incredibly tasty. I happen to like the heat, but for my family I would reduce the red pepper by half or so because it's pretty spicy. Otherwise, the flavors blend together beautifully and it's really easy to make.

Rating: 3
