Rating: 3
This is delicious even with canned tomatoes. I used only 1/2 tsp. red pepper flakes and it was still pretty spicy. Also added some strips of fresh red pepper with the fennel. A great easy meal.

Rating: 3
Actually, I would give this a 3 and 1/2 -- because of its simplicity as well as taste. I did cut the red pepper flakes to 3/4 teaspoon rather than 3/4 tablespoon and the olive oil to 4 Tablespoons.

Rating: 4
This dish is fantastic and very easy to put together! The key here is to use fresh garden tomatoes (I combined several varieties of heirloom tomatoes) and don't overcook the shrimp. Based on the previous review I cut the red pepper down to 1 teaspoon (3/4 Tbsp. seemed like a lot to me too) and it was mild. I think you could easily add more hot pepper to it according to taste. If you're counting calories I think you could cut back on the olive oil a bit with good results. A new favorite!

Rating: 0
I can't believe that no one else found this recipe scaldingly spicy! I cut the red pepper in half, and we still found it to be on the border of being inedible! I can't imagine what would have happened had I used the full recommended amount. I am going to try this recipe again, and cut down even more on the red pepper---then I expect it will be a 3- or 4-fork recipe. Except for the mouth-burning, it was delicious.

